div.div: Accessing a member's banner in discord.py

In discord.py v2.0 you can use # You may have to re-fetch the user for the banner to work properly user = await bot.fetch_user(user.id) (1 more line was trimmed) Before v2.0, there is a hacky way to get the banner by directly using the API req = await bot.http.request(discord.http.Route("GET", "/users/{uid}", uid=user.id)) banner_id = req["banner"] (7 more lines were trimmed) To install discord.py v2.0 you should run pip install -U git+https://github.com/Rapptz/discord.py
